thread.title: Cowboys' Dak Prescott tops Ezekiel Elliott for NFL offensive rookie of the year
thread.title_full: Cowboys' Dak Prescott tops Ezekiel Elliott for NFL offensive rookie of the year

author: delawareonline.com
title: Cowboys' Dak Prescott tops Ezekiel Elliott for NFL offensive rookie of the year
text:
MORE Score one for Dak Prescott over Ezekiel Elliott.
The Dallas Cowboys quarterback defeated his teammate and fellow rookie in being named the NFL's offensive rookie of the year Saturday.
Prescott went on stage at the NFL Honors ceremony to accept the awards with Elliott and remarked, "Do we have a knife to cut this in half?"
Prescott earned 28.5 of the 50 votes, with Elliott picking up the remaining 21.5.
The fourth-round pick from Mississippi State stepped in for Tony Romo and supplanted the veteran as starter, leading the Cowboys to a 13-3 record and No. 1 seed in the NFC. He threw for 3,667 yards and 23 touchdowns with just four interceptions.
Elliott, the No. 4 overall pick out of Ohio State, led the NFL in rushing with 1,631 yards and 15 touchdowns.
